The paper deals with distributed power control in MIMO systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The use of linear precoding also suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) aspect. The paper also involves optimization (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques in achieving maximum point-to-point information rate.
